DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SAUGUS WOMAN KILLED WHEN CAR STRIKES TREE 
A Saugus woman was killed Monday morning after she lost control of her car on a 
Santa Clarita Valley street and crashed into a tree, the Los Angeles County 
Sheriff's Department said. 
Nona McGraw, 34, was killed about 2 a.m. when her southbound car went out of 
control on Bouquet Canyon Road and hit a tree near Hob Avenue, deputies said. 
